\subsection{Local root number}
\begin{definition}\label{ec.local_root_number}
\uses{cmf,cmf.atkin-lehner,ec,ec.additive_reduction,ec.good_reduction,ec.nonsplit_multiplicative_reduction,ec.split_multiplicative_reduction,nf,nf.prime}
The local root number of an {{ KNOWL('ec', 'elliptic curve') }} $E$ over a {{ KNOWL('nf', 'number field') }} at a {{KNOWL('nf.prime', 'prime')}} $\mathfrak p$ is the sign of the local functional equation of $E$.  This is equal to $+1$ at primes of {{KNOWL('ec.good_reduction', 'good')}} or {{KNOWL('ec.nonsplit_multiplicative_reduction', 'non-split multiplicative reduction')}}, $-1$ at primes of {{KNOWL('ec.split_multiplicative_reduction', 'split multiplicative reduction')}}, and at primes of {{KNOWL('ec.additive_reduction', 'additive reduction')}} is $\pm1$ with no simple characterization. 

For an elliptic curve defined over $\Q$, the root number at a prime $p$ is also equal to the eigenvalue of the associated {{ KNOWL('cmf.atkin-lehner', 'Atkin-Lehner involution') }} for the associated {{KNOWL('cmf', 'modular form')}}.
\end{definition}


